<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>A plain <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.54</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.28</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.50</measure>).</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>ll. 1-10, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.045</measure>; ll.11 f., <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.025</measure>. Ligatures: <foreign lang="grc">ΗΝ</foreign>, l.2, l.5. Circular stops before and after <foreign lang="grc">ΑΥΡ</foreign>.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0211" notAfter="0217" exact="both">A.D. 211-217</date>
<rs type="criteria">Reign</rs></p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><name type="  " reg="Ἰουλία">Ἰουλία<unclear reason="damage">ν</unclear></name>  <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="2"/><name reg="Σεβαστός">Σεβαστ<hi rend="ligature">ὴ<unclear reason="damage">ν</unclear></hi></name></persName><lb n="3"/>  <space unit="character" extent="1" dim="horizontal"/>  <w lemma="μήτηρ">μητέρα</w>  <space unit="character" extent="1" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="4"/><w lemma="κάστρον">κάστρων</w>  <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w><lb n="5"/><w lemma="δῆμος">δῆμος</w>  <w lemma="ὁ">τ<hi rend="ligature">ὴν</hi></w>  <lb n="6"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <w lemma="ἑαυτοῦ">ἑαυτοῦ</w>    <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="7"/><w lemma="εὐεργέτις">εὐεργέτιν</w>  <lb n="8"/><w lemma="ἐκ">ἐξ</w>  <w lemma="ἀπόλειψις">ἀπολείψε<lb n="9" type="worddiv"/>ως</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Φλάβιος">Φλαβίου</name>  <lb n="10"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <name reg="Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλ<unclear reason="damage">ο</unclear>υ</name></persName>  <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="10a"/><space extent="1" unit="line" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="11"/><w lemma="ἐπιμελέω">ἐπιμεληθέντος</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Μᾶρκος">Μάρ<lb n="12" type="worddiv"/>κου</name>  <g type="stop"/>  <name reg="Αὐρήλιος" type="nomen"><expan><abbr>Αὐρ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ηλίου</supplied></expan></name>  <g type="stop"/>  <name reg="Χρήσιμος">Χρησίμου</name>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w><lb n="13"/><space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Ἀπολλώνιος">Ἀπολλωνίου</name></persName></persName>    <space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  </ab>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Julia Augusta mother of the military camps: the People (put up the statue of) their benefactress, from the bequest of Flavius Attalos. Marcus Aurelius Chresimos son of Apollonios took responsibility. </p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>A statue of Caracalla (<xref type="inscription" n="1312" href="120641">12.641</xref>=75.326) which is a pair to this, was found in the same area; a further statue of Caracalla (<xref type="inscription" n="1308" href="120326">12.326</xref>=MAMA 451) was set up from the same bequest; but only Julia Domna is described as a benefactor, although there is no indication of what she might have done</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p> <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Walls, South (east part)</rs>: reused in the stretch excavated in 1975.</rs> <rs type="origLocation">Unknown</rs><rs type="lastLocation">Museum</rs>
</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Preliminary transcription (Reynolds); publications</p>
</div><div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Recorded (lines 1-10 only) by the MAMA expedition in 1934. Excavated by the NYU expedition in 1975 (catalogue no. <rs type="invNo">75.325</rs>; SBI <rs type="sbi">34</rs>).</p>
</div>
